      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WONDERING SPIRIT (4) brought strong form to Cranbourne on resumption and was beaten 1L over 1500m. Tackled tougher at Caulfield Heath following and didn't finish it off. This suits better and he maps for the run of the race. Looks well placed to post his second win. IL CIELO (2) won easily over this trip at Seymour from the speed and then was just pipped as favourite at Werribee. Keeps the 4kg claim and is a decent chance to bounce. LANE CHANGER (9) peaks and is still shy of his best. Advantaged by an inside gate and has a key gear switch. Rates well and will be right in it. POSITIVO (6) is also going well enough to feature. Keeps improving and finally draws an inside barrier. TASMAN PARK (7) is better than the form line suggests. This grade suits better and the blinkers go on again.",
